# Code ownership — GitHub auto-requests review from the owner of every path a PR touches.
#
# ⚠️ PLACEHOLDER HANDLES. The @OWNER-* names below are NOT real GitHub accounts. Replace each
# with a real GitHub username (`@octocat`) or team (`@org/team`) before this file does anything —
# GitHub silently ignores an owner it cannot resolve, so an unfilled placeholder = no enforced
# review. Owners must have write access to the repo for the auto-request to fire.
#
# Rules are matched bottom-of-file-last: the LAST matching pattern wins, so the catch-all sits at
# the top and the most specific paths at the bottom.

# Catch-all: everything not claimed by a more specific rule below.
*                           @OWNER-maintainers

# ── Frontend ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The BFF (FastAPI backend-for-frontend) — the HTTP contract seam. A change here can break the
# web app's generated types; the web owner should see contract PRs too (added below).
/apps/frontend/             @OWNER-frontend

# The React/Vite web app. More specific than /apps/frontend/, so it wins for files under web/.
/apps/frontend/web/         @OWNER-frontend-web

# The exported OpenAPI contract + generated client types: changing these is changing the seam
# between the two owners above, so both review.
/apps/frontend/web/openapi.json        @OWNER-frontend @OWNER-frontend-web
/apps/frontend/web/src/api/            @OWNER-frontend @OWNER-frontend-web
